When trying to proxy remoting transparent proxy for an interface type we get an exception (MissingMethodException) when creating the proxy. Was working in version 2.5 but was broked by a change in CreateInterfaceProxyWithTargetInterface method in ProxyGenerator class. Reproduced with version 3.1 and 3.2, was introduced in 3.1.0 RC (2012-07-08).

Working line (version 2.5):
{code}if (target != null && interfaceToProxy.IsAssignableFrom(target.GetType()) == false)
{
  //check if we have remoting proxy at hand...
  if (RemotingServices.IsTransparentProxy(target))
...{code}

Broken line ('''IsInstanceOfType return true for transparent proxy''', so the code for .net remoting isnt executed):
{code}if (target != null && interfaceToProxy.IsInstanceOfType(target) == false)
{
  //check if we have remoting proxy at hand...
    if (RemotingServices.IsTransparentProxy(target)) (
...{code}

This cause a crash because it doesnt use the .net remoting code written in this method (using Type.GetConstructors() instead of Activator.CreateInstance that fail with remoting proxy).

